						               													<description>Inside the box is an association party game where players need to guess what&amp;rsquo;s inside the box.&amp;#10;Every round one of the players becomes the leader and finds out which package others have to find. The leader gives their associations, while others have to make a guess.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On the board there's a 5x5 grid of package cards.&amp;#10;Each round one player (the leader) takes a card showing a placement of the right package. The leader then takes two category cards and places them one by one between the &amp;quot;plus&amp;quot; and the &amp;quot;minus&amp;quot; cards. These are their associations concerning the connection of the category with the right package.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Now other players make their guesses: they can put their tokens on one of the cards, in-between 2 cards or even in-between 4 cards.&amp;#10;After each guessing phase the leader adds one category to the board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When the players are out of their tokens, the leader reveals the placement card and explains their associations if they want to &amp;ndash; the round ends.&amp;#10;Each player gets victory points for their tokens that were placed anywhere near the right package, while the leader gets the points for each player's closest guess.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to get 25 points wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
